Egyptian Stocks: EFG-Hermes Holding and Lecico Egypt Are Active

-- B y   A h m e d   A .   N a m a t a l l a
-- 
2011-07-07T13:38:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-07/egyptian-stocks-efg-hermes-holding-and-lecico-egypt-are-active.html
Egypt’s benchmark  EGX 30 Index (EGX30)  rose
for the fourth time this week, advancing 0.8 percent to 5,360.34
at the 2:30 p.m. close in Cairo. The measure has retreated 0.2
percent this week.  The following shares rose or fell in Cairo. Symbols are in
parentheses.  EFG-Hermes Holding SAE (HRHO EY) gained 2.6 percent, the
most in more than three weeks, to 20.93 Egyptian pounds. Egypt’s
biggest publicly traded investment bank received regulatory
approval to distribute one free share for every four held.  Lecico Egypt SAE (LCSW)   declined 2.4 percent to 10.94
pounds, the lowest level since May 16. The Alexandria, Egypt-
based manufacturer of sanitary ware said the first phase of
“porcelain body” output at a new plant has been delayed due to
the political unrest. Trial production has started at the plant,
located Borg El-Arab,  Egypt .  To contact the reporters on this story:
Ahmed A Namatalla in Cairo at 
 anamatalla@bloomberg.net ;  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
